Captain says we're moving out.

04:48.400 --> 04:49.879
So...

04:54.880 --> 04:58.190
Hey, that cat needs a friend.
And a hug.

04:59.200 --> 05:01.839
<i>It was just before Desert Storm.</i>

05:02.040 --> 05:05.271
<i>We were on a routine recon</i>
<i>inside Iraqi-controlled terrain,</i>

05:05.480 --> 05:07.198
<i>assessing enemy troop strength</i>

05:07.400 --> 05:11.552
<i>for what Saddam Hussein promised</i>
<i>would be the mother of all wars.</i>

05:12.880 --> 05:15.269
<i>I'm in the lead vehicle</i>
<i>with Sergeant Shaw</i>

05:15.480 --> 05:18.517
<i>and our guide, a civilian contractor.</i>

05:18.720 --> 05:21.393
<i>The night is clear.</i>
<i>Stars, but no moon.</i>

05:24.240 --> 05:25.195
Ambush!

05:28.960 --> 05:30.359
Hang on.

05:37.400 --> 05:39.789
Exit the vehicle.
On me! On me!

05:40.200 --> 05:41.519
Get a flare up, sergeant.

05:50.360 --> 05:53.557
Enemy dismount! Go after, go after!
Stay left!

05:53.760 --> 05:55.159
Covering, covering, covering!

05:55.360 --> 05:56.759
Bear right!

05:56.960 --> 05:58.712
Move it, move it, move it!

06:16.360 --> 06:17.793
Captain Marco!

06:20.080 --> 06:21.308
<i>Sir?</i>

06:22.240 --> 06:23.753
Was you scared?

06:25.520 --> 06:27.317
Scared? Well...

06:27.920 --> 06:30.798
...there was really no time
to be scared.

06:31.840 --> 06:35.150
<i>With complete disregard</i>
<i>for his own life,</i>

06:35.360 --> 06:38.830
<i>Sergeant Raymond Shaw</i>
<i>engaged single-handedly</i>

06:39.400 --> 06:41.231
<i>an entire company of the enemy.</i>

06:45.280 --> 06:48.078
Sergeant Shaw was awarded
the Medal of Honor.

06:48.280 --> 06:50.669
I signed the recommendation myself.

06:51.960 --> 06:53.552
Yes, sir.

06:53.760 --> 06:55.557
Were you wounded?

06:55.760 --> 06:56.909
I was, I was injured.

06:57.440 --> 07:00.591
Concussion, lost focus.
Sergeant Shaw, he took command.

07:00.800 --> 07:02.153
Major?

07:03.000 --> 07:05.878
- Yes.
- Did your unit sustain any casualties?

07:06.080 --> 07:10.198
Yes. PFC Edward Ingram,

07:10.400 --> 07:14.439
PFC Robert Baker III
were killed.

07:14.880 --> 07:17.394
Now, the Medal of Honor,
Congressional Medal of Honor,

07:17.680 --> 07:21.070
is the highest award that any soldier
could aspire to.

07:21.280 --> 07:23.874
What these brave men
that I've talked about today did

07:24.080 --> 07:26.469
should never be forgotten.

07:26.680 --> 07:31.800
Since 1917, there have only been
970 Medals awarded,

07:32.000 --> 07:35.913
out of a total of 30 million
Americans at arms.

07:36.280 --> 07:37.872
Who knows.

07:38.080 --> 07:40.594
Maybe one day,
one of you fine young men

07:41.560 --> 07:44.632
will earn that medal
in defense of this great nation.

07:46.720 --> 07:47.755
Yes.

07:47.960 --> 07:51.475
Major Marco,
on behalf of Troops 1094 and 1128,

07:51.680 --> 07:53.272
just wanna thank you

07:53.480 --> 07:55.277
for coming to speak to us
about the Medal of Honor

07:55.480 --> 07:59.155
and about your interesting experiences
in the armed forces.

07:59.360 --> 08:01.078
Thanks for listening.

08:06.880 --> 08:07.835
Thank you very much.

08:08.240 --> 08:10.674
You ever wish it had been you?

08:11.320 --> 08:13.117
I'm sorry, excuse me?

08:14.240 --> 08:16.117
Won the Medal.

08:17.120 --> 08:18.678
Been... Been the hero.

08:19.760 --> 08:23.275
Well, sir, I'm just...
I'm just proud that I was there.

08:23.480 --> 08:24.913
Thank you.

08:25.800 --> 08:27.472
Thank you very much.

08:49.080 --> 08:51.310
- Major Marco?
- Yes.

08:53.280 --> 08:54.952
Al Melvin, sir.

08:57.920 --> 08:59.512
Corporal Melvin.

09:00.680 --> 09:02.830
From your unit, Desert Storm.

09:03.760 --> 09:06.752
Corporal Melvin. How you doing?

09:09.200 --> 09:11.430
I have these dreams, sir.

09:11.920 --> 09:14.115
- Dreams?
- Yes, sir.

09:15.480 --> 09:18.677
Kuwait. It's you and me,

09:18.880 --> 09:21.917
Ingram and Baker and...

09:23.520 --> 09:24.919
...Raymond Shaw.

09:26.560 --> 09:27.754
Okay.

09:28.320 --> 09:31.710
See, I remember it happened
like you just said,

09:31.920 --> 09:33.319
and then...

09:34.240 --> 09:35.753
...I don't.

09:37.240 --> 09:38.878
Well...

09:39.080 --> 09:40.877
...we had it pretty rough
over there, Melvin.

09:41.080 --> 09:43.150
That was a long time ago.
Memories shift.

09:47.360 --> 09:49.396
Do you have dreams, sir?

09:49.760 --> 09:50.988
Everybody has dreams, corporal.

09:51.200 --> 09:52.872
No, not these.

09:53.560 --> 09:54.913
No, I don't.

09:57.760 --> 10:01.116
I write it all down.
You know, like, every night,

10:01.320 --> 10:05.632
right when I wake up,
I try to get it down.

10:05.840 --> 10:07.592
It doesn't always come together,
you know,

10:07.800 --> 10:09.074
not everything that I can remember.

10:10.120 --> 10:13.237
Maybe you should go
to the V.A. Hospital,

10:13.440 --> 10:14.509
talk to one of the doctors.

10:14.720 --> 10:16.756
- I've been to doctors, man.
- Okay.

10:20.640 --> 10:23.313
I'm just... I'm just...

10:25.040 --> 10:27.554
I'm just a little stuck, sir.

10:27.760 --> 10:30.957
Because I remember, okay, Shaw...

10:31.160 --> 10:34.152
Shaw, okay...
Shaw saving us, right...

10:34.760 --> 10:36.876
...but that doesn't make sense,
because...

10:38.840 --> 10:40.990
...that should've been you.

10:41.200 --> 10:44.192
Okay, if Shaw is in the Hummer...

10:44.640 --> 10:46.596
...the Toyota is here...

10:46.800 --> 10:49.394
All right. Just get up, get up.

10:49.600 --> 10:51.033
Listen, it's...

10:51.240 --> 10:55.074
That's over with. That's done.
Okay? You gotta move on.

10:55.280 --> 10:57.077
What I was hoping is that,
you know, maybe...

10:57.280 --> 10:58.395
You need some money
or something?

10:58.600 --> 10:59.715
- No, no, sir.
- Wait a minute.

10:59.920 --> 11:01.831
I don't need your money, man.

11:02.440 --> 11:04.556
All right. It was great to see you.

11:26.760 --> 11:29.035
Paper or plastic, sir?

11:30.560 --> 11:35.031
<i>With public anxiety being rekindled</i>
<i>by the events of Bloody Friday,</i>

11:35.240 --> 11:40.360
<i>with the war on terror continuing into</i>
<i>yet another year, no end in sight,</i>

11:40.560 --> 11:43.199
<i>the worries just continue to grow.</i>

11:43.400 --> 11:45.709
<i>Polls indicate that</i>
<i>more and more voters</i>

11:45.920 --> 11:49.037
<i>are concerned with</i>
<i>personal family safety,</i>

11:49.240 --> 11:51.151
<i>with economic security,</i>

11:51.360 --> 11:54.318
<i>fearing more and more jobs</i>
<i>going overseas</i>

11:54.520 --> 11:57.990
<i>or being taken by</i>
<i>illegal immigrants.</i>

11:58.200 --> 12:02.079
<i>They're concerned with the quality</i>
<i>of air and our water,</i>

12:02.280 --> 12:05.636
<i>the degradation caused by the</i>
<i>rollback in environmental regulations,</i>

12:05.840 --> 12:08.991
<i>by religious and racial polarization,</i>

12:09.200 --> 12:13.591
<i>with the drumbeat of body bags</i>
<i>coming from all over the globe.</i>

12:13.800 --> 12:16.997
<i>The American people are ready</i>
<i>for a new agenda.</i>

12:17.200 --> 12:21.830
<i>But because this party is so</i>
<i>divided on so many issues,</i>

12:22.040 --> 12:25.874
<i>the choice of a vice presidential</i>
<i>nominee may very well be</i>

12:26.080 --> 12:29.868
<i>the unifying factor for delegates</i>
<i>at this convention.</i>

12:30.240 --> 12:32.754
<i>And if this respect propels me</i>
<i>toward the nomination</i>

12:32.960 --> 12:37.238
<i>as your vice presidential candidate,</i>
<i>I will be greatly honored.</i>

12:37.560 --> 12:42.076
<i>We need to look inward,</i>
<i>attend to our own house.</i>

12:42.960 --> 12:46.350
<i>The danger to our country is not only</i>
<i>from some terrorists at large,</i>

12:46.560 --> 12:49.233
<i>terrorists who, by the way,</i>
<i>we've helped engender</i>

12:49.560 --> 12:52.279
<i>with 20 years</i>
<i>of failed foreign policy.</i>

12:52.480 --> 12:57.076
<i>No, the real danger</i>
<i>is from suspending civil liberties,</i>

12:57.520 --> 12:59.875
<i>gutting the Bill of Rights,</i>
<i>allowing our fear</i>

13:00.080 --> 13:02.275
<i>to destroy our democratic ideals,</i>

13:02.480 --> 13:06.234
<i>because once we start overturning</i>
<i>our constitutional protections,</i>

13:06.440 --> 13:07.919
<i>our enemies have won.</i>

13:11.200 --> 13:12.758
Raymond?

13:12.960 --> 13:14.757
- There he is.
- Darling.

13:14.960 --> 13:18.475
What, were you gonna make me
stand out there like room service?

13:22.240 --> 13:26.472
I asked downstairs and Miss Freeman,
your wrangler, helpful Miss Freeman,

13:26.680 --> 13:30.389
she said you were up here
practicing your speech.

13:30.600 --> 13:32.591
I don't honestly understand why

13:32.800 --> 13:35.473
you insist upon
isolating yourself, Raymond.

13:35.680 --> 13:37.716
People adore you,
they crave your company,

13:37.920 --> 13:39.273
and yet here you are,

13:39.480 --> 13:41.710
holed up as if you were some sort of

13:41.920 --> 13:45.390
emotionally challenged individual
like your father.

13:45.600 --> 13:50.151
Shut up, Tom.
Instead of Raymond Prentiss Shaw,

13:50.720 --> 13:52.915
handsome, intelligent,

13:53.120 --> 13:55.998
people-loving war hero
with a great deal to offer his party.

13:56.200 --> 13:58.350
- No.
- And his country.

13:58.560 --> 13:59.595
No.

13:59.800 --> 14:01.438
- No, what?
- No.

14:01.640 --> 14:03.119
I haven't even asked you
a question yet.

14:03.320 --> 14:04.992
No to the question
you're going to ask.

14:05.200 --> 14:07.156
No to all of the questions
you pretend to want to ask.

14:07.360 --> 14:08.429
Your hair is too flat.

14:08.640 --> 14:10.471
And no, you may not engage
in your usual backdoor

14:10.680 --> 14:11.590
And that tie...

14:11.800 --> 14:14.189
political thuggery to shovel me
onto the presidential ticket.

14:14.560 --> 14:17.518
Tie's wrong. Something less busy.

14:19.080 --> 14:21.150
Oh, you're not interested.

14:21.360 --> 14:24.193
Of course I'm interested.
I wouldn't be here if I wasn't.

14:24.400 --> 14:26.630
But not if it means attacking
the reputation

14:26.840 --> 14:28.432
of a statesman like Tom Jordan,

14:28.640 --> 14:30.995
which I am sure
was part of your plan.

14:31.200 --> 14:36.718
Excuse me, when have I ever
attacked Senator Jordan, despite...

14:37.560 --> 14:38.549
Despite what?

14:39.640 --> 14:41.551
Despite the shameful way
his daughter toyed with you

14:41.760 --> 14:43.876
that summer at the shore.

14:45.800 --> 14:48.109
You chased her away, Mother,
let's not have any illusions about...

14:48.320 --> 14:50.595
She wasn't in your league, but if that's
the way you choose to remember it...

14:50.800 --> 14:52.916
You destroyed any possibility
of us ever...

14:53.120 --> 14:56.430
Honey, you are oversimplifying things
a little bit, but it's okay.

14:56.720 --> 14:58.756
I'll stay out of it.

15:00.000 --> 15:01.194
You have my word.

15:03.280 --> 15:06.590
<i>Thank you. Thank you.</i>

15:08.240 --> 15:11.789
<i>I think you all know my mother,</i>
<i>Senator Eleanor Prentiss Shaw.</i>

15:14.360 --> 15:17.238
<i>And some of you, no doubt,</i>
<i>remember my father,</i>

15:17.440 --> 15:20.273
<i>the late Senator John Shaw.</i>

15:22.680 --> 15:26.559
<i>I've been honored to serve</i>
<i>my two terms in Congress.</i>

15:26.760 --> 15:28.796
<i>But I also grew up on the Hill.</i>

15:29.000 --> 15:32.072
<i>I've seen how the game is played</i>
<i>by professionals,</i>

15:32.280 --> 15:33.952
<i>how deals are struck,</i>

15:34.160 --> 15:37.311
<i>committees bullied,</i>
<i>agendas bought and sold.</i>

15:37.520 --> 15:41.229
<i>And with apologies to my mother,</i>
<i>I wish to remain an amateur.</i>

15:42.800 --> 15:46.998
<i>I believe democracy</i>
<i>is not negotiable.</i>

15:49.200 --> 15:53.990
<i>I believe that freedom from fear</i>
<i>in the world at large and here at home</i>

15:54.200 --> 15:56.430
<i>is not negotiable.</i>

15:59.440 --> 16:03.194
<i>I know how much Americans</i>
<i>have to fear today.</i>

16:03.400 --> 16:05.834
<i>But I can tell you</i>
<i>that I've been there.</i>

16:06.640 --> 16:09.677
<i>I've faced the enemy firsthand</i>
<i>on the battlefront.</i>

16:10.640 --> 16:12.915
<i>I know what it is to be afraid.</i>

16:13.760 --> 16:16.991
<i>But I am living proof</i>
<i>that we can win.</i>

16:17.720 --> 16:20.075
<i>We can prevail.</i>

16:21.520 --> 16:27.197
<i>We must secure tomorrow today.</i>
<i>Thank you.</i>

16:34.320 --> 16:35.594
- Bluffing?
- That was the inference.

16:35.800 --> 16:37.836
They should be down on their fat,
white knees, thanking me

16:38.040 --> 16:40.235
for saving this party from
committing political seppuku.

16:40.440 --> 16:42.670
You gave them every opportunity
to do the right thing, senator.

16:42.880 --> 16:46.111
No. I gave them one opportunity and
that was unusually generous of me.

16:46.520 --> 16:47.953
See if you can get ahold of
Bob Arthur,

16:48.160 --> 16:49.752
because I'm gonna wanna
meet with him.

16:49.960 --> 16:51.473
Thank you very much
for arranging this.

16:51.680 --> 16:53.352
- I appreciate it.
- Sure.

16:55.440 --> 16:57.032
- Mr. Secretary.
- Senator.

16:57.240 --> 16:59.196
Thank you very much
for taking this meeting.

16:59.400 --> 17:02.597
- Good to see you again.
- Leona. So nice to see you, Leona.

17:02.800 --> 17:05.233
Buddy. Gentlemen.

17:06.280 --> 17:08.396
No, I thought we settled it
this morning.

17:08.599 --> 17:10.352
All right, I'll keep you posted.

17:14.400 --> 17:16.277
The decision is final.

17:16.480 --> 17:18.516
Thank you very much.

17:19.440 --> 17:22.000
- How's Jeanine?
- Senator.

17:23.560 --> 17:25.391
Tom Jordan's on the ticket.

17:25.599 --> 17:27.954
Now, we don't need your blessing,

17:28.160 --> 17:29.195
but we'd like it.

17:30.760 --> 17:34.196
Okay, so before we get started,
I'm just...

17:34.640 --> 17:36.756
I'm dying to know...

17:37.720 --> 17:43.158
...which genius hatched the idea of
pairing a sound bite from Nebraska

17:43.360 --> 17:46.636
with a relic who thinks that keeping
suicide bombers off our buses

17:46.840 --> 17:49.752
is unconstitutional.
Was it you, Gordy?

17:50.400 --> 17:53.278
All the research indicates
that an Arthur-Jordan ticket

17:53.480 --> 17:54.913
sits quite well
with the American people.

17:55.120 --> 17:57.554
"Sits quite well"
translates into how many votes?

17:57.760 --> 17:59.910
Your son is largely unknown
outside of New York.

18:00.160 --> 18:03.470
I mean, his public service,
his congressional record,

18:03.680 --> 18:05.318
while commendable,
is not the kind of thing...

18:05.520 --> 18:06.430
My son is a war hero.

18:06.640 --> 18:09.393
Governor Arthur has agreed
to consider Raymond

18:09.600 --> 18:11.318
for a cabinet-level post.

18:11.520 --> 18:12.919
We didn't come here
to have a discussion.

18:13.120 --> 18:14.439
Did we come here
to have a discussion?

18:14.640 --> 18:17.518
Ellie, you don't have the votes
to block this.

18:17.720 --> 18:20.029
Not even to push the nomination
to a second ballot.

18:20.240 --> 18:22.515
Oh, Jim, even running against
this cut-and-fold vice president,

18:22.720 --> 18:26.508
with his party's record of
abysmal failure at home and abroad,

18:26.720 --> 18:30.349
Governor Arthur is still unelectable
to the presidency...

18:30.560 --> 18:31.788
...without help.

18:32.000 --> 18:35.151
Consider, that our intrepid Arthur

18:35.640 --> 18:38.029
can hold on to his own home ground,
and the Northeast,

18:38.240 --> 18:41.152
and even California,
we are still dead across the South.

18:41.360 --> 18:43.078
He's not dead completely
in the South, senator...

18:43.280 --> 18:45.794
And the Southwest,
where they win by landslides.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.069
I mean, you know this.

18:47.280 --> 18:49.555
Your focus groups,
your polls all tell you this.

18:49.760 --> 18:51.113
They back me up, right?

18:51.320 --> 18:53.754
Now, you're counting on
Tom Jordan to help you get

18:53.960 --> 18:55.791
the black vote, women
and college kids.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.116
My gut instinct says he won't,

18:58.320 --> 19:03.394
and on Arthur to somehow hold
the centre, where he is soft at best.

19:03.600 --> 19:06.034
We're confident
this is a winning ticket, Ellie.

19:06.240 --> 19:08.629
What's your margin of error, Vaughn?

19:08.840 --> 19:10.478
Five points?

19:10.680 --> 19:12.159
Three?

19:12.360 --> 19:14.351
I can swing that, and you know it.

19:14.560 --> 19:16.915
Oh, I could swing seven
away from you.

19:17.120 --> 19:18.678
That's more than enough
to split the ticket.

19:18.880 --> 19:21.599
And deny us the White House
another four years? No.

19:21.800 --> 19:22.869
No, not even you.

19:23.080 --> 19:25.355
Not even you, senator,
will do that, you are bluffing.

19:25.560 --> 19:27.596
Oh, no, no, no, senator,
I would and I will

19:27.800 --> 19:31.315
and I will do whatever is necessary
to protect America

19:31.520 --> 19:34.080
from anyone who opposes her.

19:34.280 --> 19:36.999
I can't...
Am I the only person in this room

19:37.200 --> 19:38.838
who's been reading
these NSA reports?

19:39.040 --> 19:41.270
- I've read them.
- All right, then you know,

