Good.

38:05.520 --> 38:07.238
Excellent.

38:07.440 --> 38:09.749
Releasing implant.

38:09.960 --> 38:12.349
There. That wasn't so bad,
was it, Raymond?

38:12.560 --> 38:13.788
No, sir.

38:14.440 --> 38:16.635
That's good. No decay, no slippage.

38:16.840 --> 38:20.879
Everything seems to be
in flawless working condition.

38:45.680 --> 38:47.511
Now, Raymond.

38:47.760 --> 38:51.150
Can you remember the deaths
of Private Baker and Private Ingram?

38:51.360 --> 38:52.315
Yes, sir.

38:52.560 --> 38:54.949
Good. Can you describe them
for me, please?

38:55.160 --> 38:58.072
<i>We're on a routine recon</i>
<i>inside Iraqi-controlled terrain,</i>

38:58.280 --> 39:00.669
<i>assessing troop strength.</i>

39:02.080 --> 39:06.232
"We're on a routine recon
inside Iraqi-controlled terrain,

39:06.440 --> 39:07.759
assessing troop strength."

39:07.960 --> 39:10.474
The mission ends without incident.
We're heading back...

39:10.680 --> 39:13.319
"Toward the command.
The night is clear. Stars..."

39:13.560 --> 39:16.757
The night is clear.
Stars, but no moon.

39:17.320 --> 39:18.514
<i>The patrol is ambushed.</i>

39:18.720 --> 39:21.837
<i>We're engaged unexpectedly by</i>
<i>ground forces with helicopter support.</i>

39:22.040 --> 39:24.759
<i>RPG incoming, mortar fire.</i>

39:25.080 --> 39:26.559
"Captain..."

39:28.120 --> 39:30.350
Captain Marco
is knocked unconscious.

39:30.560 --> 39:34.314
In the ensuing firefight, Eddie Ingram
gets himself separated to the left.

39:35.040 --> 39:37.076
<i>Baker goes after him.</i>

39:37.280 --> 39:39.316
<i>An incoming mortar shell</i>
<i>kills them both instantly</i>

39:39.520 --> 39:42.796
<i>before I am able to locate and</i>
<i>eliminate the source of the ordnance.</i>

39:44.560 --> 39:47.791
<i>Captain. Captain Marco.</i>

39:48.000 --> 39:49.353
<i>Help me.</i>

39:56.760 --> 39:59.479
Pardon me. Is this seat taken?

40:00.080 --> 40:03.470
I see the captain enjoys
the road less traveled.

40:20.240 --> 40:22.196
Paper or plastic?

40:24.160 --> 40:27.277
Oh, come on.
From the grocery store.

40:27.480 --> 40:30.358
You know, at the checkout stand.
Paper or plastic girl, that's me.

40:30.560 --> 40:31.959
"Paper or plastic, sir?"

40:33.560 --> 40:34.913
I see you there all the time.

40:35.120 --> 40:37.509
Bennett Marco.
Checks from First National Bank.

40:37.720 --> 40:42.316
Romance novels, instant noodles,
NoDoz and tomatoes.

40:46.240 --> 40:48.913
So anyway, I'm on vacation.

40:49.120 --> 40:51.190
Holiday in the Big Apple
and all of that.

40:51.400 --> 40:53.709
And I saw you sitting here
and I said, "Hey,

40:53.920 --> 40:56.673
why not reach out
and touch someone?"

41:00.320 --> 41:03.118
So, what, I suppose
you're heading to New York City.

41:03.320 --> 41:05.356
Yeah, yeah, I'm... Yeah.

41:05.960 --> 41:08.269
Business? Pleasure? Both?

41:08.600 --> 41:13.390
Well, I'm just... I got an old friend
up there, an old Army friend that...

41:14.320 --> 41:17.073
Well, he's in politics now
and I'm just gonna

41:17.280 --> 41:19.510
catch up on old times with him.

41:23.320 --> 41:24.833
I'm sorry, you said your name was?

41:25.720 --> 41:27.073
Eugenie.

41:28.040 --> 41:29.553
What do your friends call you?

41:29.760 --> 41:31.796
My friends, they call me Rosie.

41:32.240 --> 41:34.151
- Rosie?
- Yeah, see, my full name is

41:34.360 --> 41:35.839
Eugenie Rose.
I like the Rosie part better.

41:36.040 --> 41:38.679
Eugenie is, well...

41:39.200 --> 41:40.679
...fragile.

41:41.040 --> 41:44.112
Yeah, but still, when I asked you
your name, you didn't say...

41:44.560 --> 41:46.357
What did you say?
You said Eugenie.

41:46.560 --> 41:48.630
Yeah, well...

41:49.200 --> 41:53.716
...maybe I was feeling fragile
at the time.

42:02.640 --> 42:04.039
Are you okay?

42:04.240 --> 42:05.514
Excuse me.

42:51.680 --> 42:53.033
Hello, captain.

42:53.760 --> 42:55.113
Do you remember me?

43:26.040 --> 43:27.314
Ben.

43:28.160 --> 43:31.470
Hey. I'm gonna get a cab.
You want me to drop you somewhere?

43:31.680 --> 43:32.829
No, I'm okay.

43:33.040 --> 43:34.758
Okay. So your friend's
gonna meet you here, then?

43:34.960 --> 43:36.279
No.

43:37.760 --> 43:39.113
All right.

43:39.320 --> 43:42.198
El Dorado 5-9970.

43:44.520 --> 43:48.149
It's my cell phone number,
in case you ever... You know.

43:48.360 --> 43:50.271
I like to say it the old-fashioned way.

43:50.480 --> 43:53.711
Can you remember or should I write it
on your chest with a Sharpie?

43:54.560 --> 43:56.676
- I'll remember.
- Okay.

43:57.360 --> 43:59.590
Hey, you're kind of...

44:00.240 --> 44:02.629
You need somewhere to go
to freshen up?

44:04.360 --> 44:05.952
<i>Pentagon watchdogs</i>
<i>today accused</i>

44:06.160 --> 44:08.435
<i>the private equity fund</i>
<i>Manchurian Global</i>

44:08.640 --> 44:12.315
<i>of grossly overpricing plasma</i>
<i>and other critical medical supplies</i>

44:12.520 --> 44:14.511
<i>during the recent</i>
<i>Indonesian incursion,</i>

44:14.720 --> 44:18.838
<i>even as the company secured</i>
<i>a half-billion-dollar no-bid contract</i>

44:19.040 --> 44:22.032
<i>to provide combat support services</i>
<i>to American soldiers</i>

44:22.240 --> 44:24.310
<i>preparing to mobilize in Sri Lanka.</i>

44:36.320 --> 44:38.038
There you go.

44:38.840 --> 44:40.114
Come on in.

44:40.320 --> 44:42.788
This is my cousin's apartment.

44:43.200 --> 44:45.031
- Is she here?
- No.

44:45.240 --> 44:47.196
Be it ever so humble.

44:47.600 --> 44:49.716
No place like home, right?

44:49.960 --> 44:53.032
Believe it or not, there's a view.

44:53.240 --> 44:56.198
Go to the fire escape
and tilt your head up,

44:56.440 --> 44:58.510
you can almost see a tree.

45:00.600 --> 45:02.795
- Can I get you something to drink?
- No, I'm fine.

45:05.320 --> 45:07.959
I've got some dieter's tea.

45:08.160 --> 45:11.630
It's great for your metabolism,
if you're into that.

45:11.840 --> 45:16.595
Or some tomato juice. No? All right.

45:17.280 --> 45:18.838
Or...

45:19.040 --> 45:20.109
...some water?

45:20.560 --> 45:22.596
- No, thank you.
- I'm sorry.

45:23.680 --> 45:26.035
I'm nervous.
I yak when I get nervous.

45:27.120 --> 45:28.792
Where is she, your cousin?

45:30.080 --> 45:31.957
She's on tour with <i>Dreamgirls</i>.

45:42.800 --> 45:43.949
Hey, are you okay?

45:46.480 --> 45:47.799
Yeah.

45:50.480 --> 45:53.392
Look, I'm sorry about
what happened earlier.

45:53.600 --> 45:56.034
You don't have to apologize to me.

45:57.040 --> 45:59.110
I'll make you some tea.

46:36.560 --> 46:39.916
Jesus. Where's the lemon? Okay.

46:40.600 --> 46:44.115
- You okay in there?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

46:44.720 --> 46:47.871
You know, I left you some towels
in there, did you see them?

46:51.680 --> 46:53.716
- What was that?
- Dropped my bag.

47:01.040 --> 47:02.439
Ben?

47:03.680 --> 47:05.398
Are you okay in there?

47:05.840 --> 47:07.114
Earth to Ben.

47:07.840 --> 47:09.114
Yeah.

47:09.400 --> 47:12.437
- You sure everything's all right?
- Yes.

47:15.200 --> 47:16.679
Ben?

47:25.720 --> 47:27.278
Ben?

47:27.960 --> 47:29.632
Ben?

47:30.520 --> 47:31.635
Ben.

47:36.000 --> 47:37.319
Ben?

47:59.960 --> 48:01.234
What are you doing?

48:05.440 --> 48:07.078
Did you see that?

48:10.720 --> 48:12.756
What I had in my hand.

48:16.680 --> 48:19.399
<i>I wasn't hallucinating, Delp.</i>
<i>I held it in my hand.</i>

48:19.600 --> 48:21.875
That's what they all say, Marco.

48:22.080 --> 48:25.038
Some wicked shit got sprayed
on you guys during Desert Storm.

48:25.600 --> 48:28.592
Besides all the depleted uranium,
I mean.

48:29.240 --> 48:31.196
I personally know of
a couple of Rangers

48:31.400 --> 48:34.039
who swear that they see only
in tertiary colors now,

48:34.240 --> 48:37.198
- Delp.
- And can pick up sports talk radio

48:37.400 --> 48:40.710
in their cortical block if they get
too close to a Con-Ed transformer.

48:41.120 --> 48:42.917
It's not Gulf War Syndrome.

48:49.480 --> 48:55.350
The Army did try this
tiny, implantable ID thing.

48:57.120 --> 49:00.032
You could imbed it under the skin,
then scan it like a bar code

49:00.240 --> 49:02.754
for medical emergency information:

49:03.200 --> 49:05.316
Blood type, DNA.

49:05.520 --> 49:07.476
Well, the Army never put one in me.

49:11.160 --> 49:13.310
That you know of, man.

49:15.720 --> 49:17.392
That you know of.

49:27.680 --> 49:30.831
<i>U.S. Planes bombed selected sites</i>
<i>in Guinea today, acting on intelligence</i>

49:31.040 --> 49:34.237
<i>that the African nation's military</i>
<i>regime had secretly resumed</i>

49:34.440 --> 49:35.998
<i>its chemical weapons program.</i>

49:36.200 --> 49:38.316
<i>The secretary of defense declined</i>
<i>to comment on the attack,</i>

49:38.520 --> 49:40.317
<i>saying only that the mission</i>
<i>was successful,</i>

49:40.520 --> 49:43.432
<i>targets acquired, that all American</i>
<i>personnel involved here</i>

49:43.640 --> 49:46.916
<i>- were home safe and sound.</i>
<i>- Striking transportation workers...</i>

49:48.080 --> 49:52.278
My dreams seem more real to me

49:52.480 --> 49:55.756
than what I actually remember
happening over there. It's like...

49:57.920 --> 50:03.119
It's like somewhere along the line
I got brainwashed or something and...

50:05.400 --> 50:08.039
I'm just, like, all scrambled up.

50:09.160 --> 50:11.116
We have all been
brainwashed, Marco.

50:12.280 --> 50:15.477
As for somebody
imbedding electric probes

50:15.680 --> 50:20.071
and computer chips in your brain
to make you do things,

50:20.320 --> 50:22.038
it's horseshit, man.

50:24.680 --> 50:26.033
A little electroshock...

50:26.960 --> 50:30.350
...and sleep deprivation will do
the trick for a fraction of the price.

50:30.560 --> 50:32.471
Ask the Uzbeks.

50:33.640 --> 50:35.517
What about my dreams?

50:36.800 --> 50:39.872
What if all this is your dream...

50:40.960 --> 50:43.758
...and you are really
still back in Kuwait?

51:06.720 --> 51:09.712
- Thanks for coming out. Thank you.
- Congressman!

51:09.920 --> 51:11.433
- Congressman!
- Congressman!

51:11.640 --> 51:14.200
Congressman! Congressman!
Why do you and Governor Arthur

51:14.400 --> 51:16.118
oppose deploying troops
into Indonesia?

51:16.320 --> 51:17.719
Well, Governor Arthur and I believe

51:17.920 --> 51:19.558
we can't clean up the world
with dirty hands.

51:19.760 --> 51:21.352
Sergeant Shaw!

51:23.040 --> 51:24.678
Do you ever dream about Kuwait?

51:25.000 --> 51:26.718
Captain Marco.

51:28.560 --> 51:30.232
It's okay. It's okay.

51:30.440 --> 51:31.873
Nice to see you, sir.

51:32.120 --> 51:34.395
Good evening.
It's good to see you too.

51:34.720 --> 51:36.119
Why did you ask me about Kuwait?

51:36.320 --> 51:37.719
I didn't.
I asked you about your dreams.

51:37.920 --> 51:39.148
- Thank you, Lily.
- Congressman Shaw, I'm sorry.

51:39.360 --> 51:41.635
They wanna know if you can do
an interview with Larry King at 6?

51:41.840 --> 51:43.319
- No, no.
- No to the interview or no to 6?

51:43.520 --> 51:44.953
No. He wants to talk
about my mother. No.

51:45.160 --> 51:46.912
- Everything under control, P. J?
- Hello, sir.

51:47.160 --> 51:48.752
Good to see you.

51:49.000 --> 51:50.877
So, captain, what can I do for you?

51:51.080 --> 51:52.433
I just need a few minutes
of your time.

51:52.640 --> 51:53.868
Congressman Shaw,
a moment, please?

51:54.080 --> 51:54.990
Private time.

51:55.200 --> 51:57.760
Unfortunately, this is as private
as it gets for me now.

51:57.960 --> 51:59.439
- I understand.
- He's all right, Will.

51:59.640 --> 52:01.551
- Come on in.
- Thank you, thank you.

52:03.040 --> 52:05.600
- Hey, George.
- There are these dreams

52:05.800 --> 52:08.439
that some of the men
from our unit have been having.

52:08.640 --> 52:09.914
Including you?

52:10.120 --> 52:11.348
Well...

52:11.960 --> 52:14.872
...it's more of a question
of what actually happened

52:15.080 --> 52:17.036
the night that our patrol
got attacked.

52:17.560 --> 52:21.633
That's easy. We're on a routine recon
inside Iraqi-controlled terrain.

52:21.840 --> 52:24.354
The patrol is ambushed.
RPG incoming, mortar fire.

52:24.560 --> 52:26.676
- You're knocked...
- Unconscious. Exactly the way...

52:26.880 --> 52:29.713
Not to cut you off, but I mean,
exactly the way that I remember it.

52:29.920 --> 52:32.593
But I dreamed something else.

52:34.160 --> 52:35.593
Am I in your dreams, captain?

52:36.480 --> 52:38.038
Yes, you are, congressman.

52:38.360 --> 52:39.429
Saving everybody?

52:39.640 --> 52:42.518
It's a whole lot more complicated
than that. Now, Corporal Melvin,

52:42.720 --> 52:45.075
he's been drawing these pictures
and he wrote down what he dreams.

52:45.280 --> 52:47.111
- Maybe if you just...
- I don't have dreams, captain.

52:48.000 --> 52:50.798
At all? You don't dream at all?
Everybody dreams, right? I mean...

52:51.000 --> 52:53.230
Look, captain, I'd like to help you,
I would, I really would,

52:53.440 --> 52:55.158
but I think you ought to
see somebody.

52:55.360 --> 52:57.316
- Somebody who specializes in...
- I've been to doctors.

52:57.800 --> 52:59.313
Well, good, that's very good,

52:59.520 --> 53:01.988
because they can probably
help you out a lot more than I can.

53:02.240 --> 53:03.798
- I don't know, but...
- Take care, captain.

53:04.000 --> 53:06.468
- Yeah. Yeah. Okay.
- Thanks for coming by.

53:12.680 --> 53:14.352
I'm not crazy, Shaw.

53:18.400 --> 53:19.879
Major.

53:22.000 --> 53:25.709
- Ben. Are you hungry?
- Starving.

53:31.160 --> 53:32.479
Well, it depends on the demographic.

53:32.720 --> 53:33.948
Excuse me.

53:35.400 --> 53:37.231
- I killed Baker?
- Well, it's a dream.

53:37.440 --> 53:39.476
I mean, it could mean
something else.

53:39.960 --> 53:42.190
It could mean I'm supposed
to think you did.

53:42.400 --> 53:46.075
No, I killed the enemy.
I didn't know them either, so...

53:46.440 --> 53:48.032
...it was okay.

53:48.760 --> 53:51.558
And anyway, I remember what we did
in Kuwait. I remember it perfectly.

53:51.760 --> 53:52.909
I just...

53:53.440 --> 53:55.749
...don't remember actually doing it.

53:56.480 --> 53:58.072
Maybe you didn't do it.

54:04.800 --> 54:06.233
No.

54:07.200 --> 54:08.713
What a thought.

54:26.080 --> 54:27.479
What?

54:32.080 --> 54:34.036
Life is so bizarre, isn't it?

54:35.040 --> 54:36.598
Which part?

54:36.800 --> 54:39.155
I don't know.
What you saw downstairs.

54:39.600 --> 54:45.277
This campaign. Politics.
My whole public life and persona.

54:46.760 --> 54:50.389
I mean, posing and grinning
like a goddamn sock puppet,

54:50.600 --> 54:53.160
shaking hands with total strangers
who must be completely blind

54:53.360 --> 54:55.635
if they can't see
what I am at the core.

54:55.840 --> 54:58.673
What my mother has made me.
A Prentiss.

54:58.880 --> 55:01.030
Ferociously a Prentiss.

55:01.600 --> 55:04.751
- But not a Shaw. No, sir.
- I see.

55:05.280 --> 55:06.793
No, you don't.

55:07.720 --> 55:08.869
You can't.

55:11.240 --> 55:13.117
I was 20 years old
before I had a friend.

55:13.320 --> 55:19.077
Worse, a girlfriend. Well, you know,
from my point of view, anyway.

55:19.440 --> 55:23.149
A friend outside of my mother's circle
of approved encounters

55:23.360 --> 55:25.396
and she...

55:27.680 --> 55:29.318
...my mother...

55:32.280 --> 55:36.558
God only knows what she told
Jocelyn to chase her away.

55:37.080 --> 55:39.594
Precipitating my sole act
of rebellion:

55:39.800 --> 55:41.552
Storming off...

55:42.320 --> 55:44.709
...and enlisting in the Army.

55:48.000 --> 55:49.353
But after the war...

55:51.280 --> 55:53.396
...I came back to her.

55:55.000 --> 55:57.070
Why did you come back?
What happened?

56:01.520 --> 56:03.238
Weren't you listening?

56:03.920 --> 56:05.797
Mother happened.

56:06.960 --> 56:09.076
You know, the truth is I hate it.

56:09.520 --> 56:11.715
I've always despised the Medal.

56:12.320 --> 56:15.517
The cloying adulation
of the little people.

56:16.480 --> 56:18.675
It's certainly...

56:18.920 --> 56:21.388
...nothing for you
to be jealous of, major.

56:21.600 --> 56:22.919
I'm not jealous.

56:23.840 --> 56:25.558
I don't have the dreams, Ben.

56:26.040 --> 56:30.192
How could you not remember
saving our unit?

56:30.760 --> 56:32.113
I do. I said I did.

56:32.320 --> 56:35.756
No, no, you didn't. You said
that you didn't remember doing it.

56:35.960 --> 56:38.190
That's what you just said
a couple minutes ago.

56:39.840 --> 56:41.956
When I think about that night...

56:43.520 --> 56:46.034
...it's as if I know what will happen.

56:47.240 --> 56:48.878
The thing is, I never seem
to get to the point

56:49.080 --> 56:52.152
where I feel that it actually
does happen.

56:52.360 --> 56:54.112
But I'm sure that's perfectly normal.

56:54.400 --> 56:57.870
Okay. Well, have you discussed this
with anyone? These discrepancies?

56:58.240 --> 57:00.310
Who would I share that with?

57:01.040 --> 57:03.315
My old Army buddies
who love and adore me

57:03.520 --> 57:05.556
for saving their
pathetically unimportant,

57:05.760 --> 57:08.115
present company excluded, asses?

57:08.560 --> 57:10.516
You could discuss it
with Army intelligence.

57:10.720 --> 57:13.996
You could go down there.
I mean, I could go with you

57:14.200 --> 57:16.270
and discuss it and you can tell them
what you remember,

57:16.480 --> 57:19.313
what you don't remember,
and they could...

57:20.040 --> 57:21.712
...run some tests.

57:24.360 --> 57:26.669
Yeah, tests. Boy.

57:26.880 --> 57:28.791
The press would have
a field day with that.

57:29.440 --> 57:32.034
Somebody put an implant inside me.
I found it this morning.

57:32.240 --> 57:34.356
I've got the hole in my back
if you wanna take a look at it.

57:34.560 --> 57:37.028
And I got a good feeling
they put one in you too.

57:42.840 --> 57:44.432
Nobody has put anything
in me, Ben.

57:44.640 --> 57:46.676
Let's prove it.
Why don't, you know...

57:46.880 --> 57:48.393
- We'll go get an x-ray...
- Look, Ben,

57:48.600 --> 57:50.318
I wanna be supportive of you. I do.

57:50.520 --> 57:52.988
But don't you think this could wait
till after the election?

57:53.200 --> 57:54.315
Why? For what?

57:54.520 --> 57:56.476
- What are you scared of?
- I'm not afraid of anything.

57:56.680 --> 57:59.319
- Then why don't we just prove it...
- Know what? I think you should leave.

57:59.520 --> 58:01.988
- I'm sorry, I really...
- Listen.

58:02.200 --> 58:06.796
Somebody got into our heads
with big steel-toe boots,

58:07.000 --> 58:09.355
cable cutters and a chainsaw
and they went to town.

58:09.560 --> 58:12.870
Neurons got... Got...
Got exposed and circuits got rewired.

58:13.080 --> 58:15.674
Our brain cells got
obliterated, Raymond.

58:15.880 --> 58:17.393
Please.

58:18.240 --> 58:20.117
You need to get help, Ben.

58:20.920 --> 58:23.036
What are you doing? Ben!

58:27.120 --> 58:28.758
Stop! Stop!

58:29.040 --> 58:30.189
Inside! Inside!

58:35.960 --> 58:36.915
Congressman!

58:42.560 --> 58:44.278
He bit him. He bit him.

58:48.560 --> 58:50.152
Get him out of here.

58:57.560 --> 58:59.073
Are you okay, sir?

59:01.600 --> 59:02.953
- Leave me alone.
- Sir, we should...

59:03.160 --> 59:04.639
Get out!

59:37.520 --> 59:39.158
We fished him out of
the Potomac River

59:39.360 --> 59:42.158
about 4:45 yesterday afternoon.

59:43.200 --> 59:45.953
What were you doing
in Al Melvin's apartment?

59:47.080 --> 59:48.559
I went to talk to him.
He wasn't home.

59:48.760 --> 59:51.638
Talk about what? Dreams?

59:54.440 --> 59:55.873
Interesting stuff.

59:56.080 --> 59:58.992
Yeah, there's hundreds
of those in his place.

59:59.200 --> 01:00:00.394
You should have your people
check it out.

01:00:00.600 --> 01:00:01.999
Oh, we'll get on that right away.

01:00:02.200 --> 01:00:05.397
Colonel Garret was kind enough
to show us the file on you, Marco.

01:00:05.600 --> 01:00:08.751
You are the real deal, aren't you?

01:00:09.960 --> 01:00:12.872
Special Forces. Rangers. Delta.

01:00:14.800 --> 01:00:16.472
I wanted to talk to Corporal Melvin

01:00:16.680 --> 01:00:20.389
to ask him some
unanswered questions about...

01:00:20.600 --> 01:00:23.160
...our reconnaissance
in Kuwait back in '91.

01:00:23.360 --> 01:00:25.112
- He wasn't home.
- Right. He wasn't there.

01:00:25.320 --> 01:00:28.710
So, what, you thought it was okay
to just break in and wait for him?

01:00:28.920 --> 01:00:30.319
I didn't kill him,
if that's where you're headed.

01:00:30.520 --> 01:00:32.112
Nobody said you did.

01:00:32.320 --> 01:00:33.719
Maybe he committed suicide.

01:00:35.720 --> 01:00:37.438
What's your obsession
with Raymond Shaw?

01:00:37.640 --> 01:00:39.153
I'm not obsessed
with Raymond Shaw.

01:00:39.360 --> 01:00:40.918
The man of his dreams.

01:00:42.400 --> 01:00:44.118
You may want to ask
your medical examiners

01:00:44.320 --> 01:00:46.117
to check Melvin's back.

01:00:46.320 --> 01:00:47.912
It's under the skin
just shy of the scapula.

01:00:48.120 --> 01:00:50.839
They may find a implant.

01:00:51.040 --> 01:00:52.598
Just under the skin, left side.

01:00:52.800 --> 01:00:54.950
If they don't look real hard,
they won't find it.

01:00:55.480 --> 01:00:57.710
They could sing that while
they're looking for it if they like.

01:00:57.920 --> 01:00:59.672
- Implants.
- That's what I said.

01:00:59.880 --> 01:01:01.472
I-M-plant.

01:01:01.680 --> 01:01:06.196
Yeah, but judging from
your file here, apparently,

01:01:06.400 --> 01:01:08.709
you don't know your shit
from your oatmeal, my friend.

01:01:08.920 --> 01:01:10.478
Excuse me. This is unnecessary.

01:01:11.200 --> 01:01:12.599
You got a problem?

01:01:13.640 --> 01:01:16.757
Psycho? You look a little angry.

01:01:17.920 --> 01:01:20.593
Maybe you wanna hit me?
Go ahead, you can do it.

01:01:21.720 --> 01:01:24.280
- Hey!
- For God's sake, Ben...

01:01:25.880 --> 01:01:26.869
He hit me.

01:01:28.120 --> 01:01:29.758
And you wanna help him?

01:01:29.960 --> 01:01:33.430
No. That would be political suicide.
Of course not.

01:01:33.920 --> 01:01:35.797
I want you to help him.

01:01:38.400 --> 01:01:41.437
I can't even imagine why.

01:01:42.160 --> 01:01:45.197
Mother, I can assure you, I am as
uncomfortable asking you to do this

01:01:45.400 --> 01:01:47.470
as you are being asked.

01:01:47.800 --> 01:01:50.268
My campaign people are getting
a restraining order against him.

01:01:50.480 --> 01:01:53.552
He's going on every security watch list,
but I won't lock him up.

01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:56.320
- I'm not pressing charges.
- What?

01:01:56.520 --> 01:01:58.590
I don't know, it's just...

01:02:02.040 --> 01:02:03.393
I don't wanna talk
about this right now.

01:02:03.600 --> 01:02:05.318
Can we get back to the campaign
and focus on something...

01:02:05.520 --> 01:02:08.751
Raymond, you don't actually
believe his story?

01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:12.312
No.

01:02:12.840 --> 01:02:14.831
But he does.

01:02:16.320 --> 01:02:18.675
And he's a fine soldier.

01:02:19.680 --> 01:02:22.274
And if his slim hold
on sanity requires

01:02:22.480 --> 01:02:24.835
that I tolerate his delusions
until he can get help, I'll do it.

01:02:25.040 --> 01:02:26.598
It doesn't diminish me.

01:02:27.200 --> 01:02:29.031
I'm not afraid of him.

01:02:30.120 --> 01:02:31.553
Raymond.

01:02:38.920 --> 01:02:42.356
How much do you actually know
about your friend?

01:03:12.560 --> 01:03:14.391
Oh, that's sad.

01:03:14.600 --> 01:03:16.431
Poor little tin soldier.

01:03:16.640 --> 01:03:18.232
Mother, please.

01:03:18.440 --> 01:03:20.908
Well, just imagine how terrified
your people were yesterday

01:03:21.120 --> 01:03:23.350
when Major Marco showed up
at campaign headquarters

01:03:23.560 --> 01:03:25.073
and you invite...

01:03:25.280 --> 01:03:27.316
My God, you invited him in.

01:03:27.920 --> 01:03:29.319
With all they know about him.

01:03:30.280 --> 01:03:32.111
I know him.

01:03:32.720 --> 01:03:34.597
I served under him.
He was a good man.

01:03:34.800 --> 01:03:37.872
Well, that's what the neighbors
always say about serial killers.

01:03:46.440 --> 01:03:49.159
You're out of here.
Shaw won't press charges.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:55.116
Someone from
Senator Eleanor Shaw's office called

01:03:55.320 --> 01:03:57.390
and intervened on your behalf.

01:03:57.600 --> 01:04:00.034
Major, you've reached the terminal end
of the Army's patience.

01:04:00.240 --> 01:04:02.754
You're relieved of duty,
effective immediately.

01:04:04.960 --> 01:04:06.598
Yes, sir.

01:04:06.800 --> 01:04:08.074
Ben,

01:04:08.280 --> 01:04:11.352
there is a young neurologist
at Walter Reed. His name is Zahn.

01:04:11.560 --> 01:04:13.710
He's had real success
with Gulf War Syndrome.

01:04:13.920 --> 01:04:15.797
You are instructed to get
your affairs in order

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:17.956
and report to him
first thing Monday morning.

01:04:43.080 --> 01:04:44.752
I thought you said you lost it.

01:04:44.960 --> 01:04:46.473
I bit a guy. I found another one.

01:04:49.120 --> 01:04:51.873
These are not supposed to exist.

01:04:58.800 --> 01:05:01.189
These are only theoretical.

01:05:06.080 --> 01:05:07.559
So, what does it do?

01:05:07.760 --> 01:05:09.990
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:13.718
I don't know.

01:05:15.960 --> 01:05:18.838
I don't wanna know.
You don't wanna know.

01:05:19.040 --> 01:05:21.679
Look, it's out of you
and you are still alive.

01:05:21.880 --> 01:05:23.916
That's the good news.

01:05:24.400 --> 01:05:25.879
What's the bad news?

01:05:28.120 --> 01:05:30.111
Maybe they know you're here.

01:05:48.160 --> 01:05:51.152
You said the Army implants,
they were for

01:05:51.360 --> 01:05:53.669
emergency medical data, right?

01:05:53.880 --> 01:05:56.440
The ones they publicized were.

01:05:57.160 --> 01:06:02.188
There was a parallel project
for all kinds of scary implantables.

01:06:02.400 --> 01:06:05.790
The Clinton watchdogs finally
freaked out about it, closed down.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:07.991
Parallel project?

01:06:08.200 --> 01:06:09.394
How did you know about that?

01:06:09.600 --> 01:06:14.196
Manchurian Global funded me
to make some of their scary shit.

01:06:14.400 --> 01:06:16.038
Heard of them?

01:06:16.880 --> 01:06:18.996
Imagine not just
a corporation, Marco,

01:06:19.200 --> 01:06:22.670
but a goddamn geopolitical
extension of policy

01:06:22.880 --> 01:06:24.996
for every president since Nixon.

01:06:25.200 --> 01:06:26.838
Cash is king, Marco.

01:06:27.040 --> 01:06:29.031
Cash is king.

01:06:40.040 --> 01:06:42.076
You sure you wanna do this?

01:06:42.280 --> 01:06:43.952
Absolutely.

01:06:46.080 --> 01:06:47.752
Because I don't.

01:06:47.960 --> 01:06:49.234
I'll owe you one.

01:06:49.440 --> 01:06:51.078
No.

01:06:51.280 --> 01:06:52.998
I still owe you.

01:06:54.080 --> 01:06:56.275
For getting me out of Albania.

01:06:56.480 --> 01:06:57.708
Albania.

01:07:03.080 --> 01:07:04.115
What are you doing?

01:07:04.320 --> 01:07:05.992
In case I forget things
I wanna remember.

01:07:10.880 --> 01:07:15.635
I'm putting you on a cocktail
of methohexitol to take the edge off.

01:07:15.840 --> 01:07:17.239
The edge off of what?

01:07:17.440 --> 01:07:21.035
Getting clarity.
Or whatever you wanna call it.

01:07:21.760 --> 01:07:25.833
ECT not being
the precise science that, say,

01:07:26.040 --> 01:07:27.917
leeching is.

01:07:28.120 --> 01:07:30.315
You don't think
this is gonna work?

01:07:30.960 --> 01:07:33.554
It's a desperation move, man.

01:07:34.200 --> 01:07:36.395
But, hey, there is a school
of thought that says

01:07:36.600 --> 01:07:38.830
a victim of induced abreaction...

01:07:39.040 --> 01:07:40.917
Here it comes.

01:08:11.200 --> 01:08:13.077
<i>The night is clear.</i>
<i>Stars, but no moon.</i>

01:08:13.280 --> 01:08:14.429
<i>The patrol is ambushed.</i>

01:08:14.640 --> 01:08:17.916
<i>We were on a routine recon</i>
<i>inside Iraqi-controlled terrain,</i>

01:08:18.120 --> 01:08:19.951
<i>assessing troop strength...</i>

01:08:20.160 --> 01:08:21.957
<i>Captain Marco was</i>
<i>knocked unconscious.</i>

01:08:22.160 --> 01:08:24.957
<i>In the ensuing firefight, Eddie Ingram</i>
<i>gets himself separated to the left.</i>

01:08:25.160 --> 01:08:26.309
<i>Baker goes after him.</i>

01:08:26.520 --> 01:08:27.635
Hello, captain.

01:08:28.640 --> 01:08:30.835
Before Sergeant Shaw
is able to locate...

01:08:31.040 --> 01:08:33.076
Eddie Ingram gets himself
separated to the left.

01:09:11.359 --> 01:09:13.430
Did you go blank on me again?

01:09:18.920 --> 01:09:20.911
He said this would happen.

01:09:22.240 --> 01:09:23.798
Who?

01:09:24.479 --> 01:09:27.118
Your German friend.
Your friend.

01:09:28.600 --> 01:09:30.033
Ben.

01:09:32.479 --> 01:09:36.109
He said it'd be like
a computer system crash.

01:09:36.319 --> 01:09:39.153
That your brain would shut down,
but it would reboot again

01:09:39.359 --> 01:09:41.510
and you'd forget all your RAM.

01:09:41.720 --> 01:09:43.631
Or most of your RAM.

01:09:49.720 --> 01:09:52.234
Do you remember me?

01:09:54.480 --> 01:09:57.870
Do you remember me?

01:09:58.920 --> 01:10:00.512
Ben?

01:10:02.080 --> 01:10:03.957
Eugenie.

01:10:08.520 --> 01:10:10.317
How did I get here?

01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:12.672
You called me.

01:10:13.600 --> 01:10:15.033
Where am I?

01:10:15.240 --> 01:10:16.798
<i>- Planning a suicide bombing.</i>

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:19.878
<i>The Mile High City has suffered</i>
<i>a series of brutal attacks</i>

01:10:20.080 --> 01:10:21.433
<i>during the past several months.</i>

01:10:21.800 --> 01:10:25.679
<i>Senator Eleanor Prentiss Shaw,</i>
<i>does it bother you at all</i>

01:10:25.880 --> 01:10:29.714
<i>that your son repudiates</i>
<i>so many of your more</i>

01:10:29.920 --> 01:10:32.514
<i>- controversial policies?</i>
<i>- No. He's his own person.</i>

01:10:32.720 --> 01:10:35.075
<i>Raymond and I may disagree</i>
<i>on certain issues,</i>

01:10:35.280 --> 01:10:38.317
<i>but I think we share</i>
<i>the same fundamental vision</i>

01:10:38.520 --> 01:10:39.873
<i>of what this country can be.</i>

01:10:40.080 --> 01:10:41.752
<i>- Which is?</i>
<i>- Better.</i>

01:10:41.960 --> 01:10:43.473
<i>Better and better.</i>

01:10:43.680 --> 01:10:45.716
<i>Safer, braver, stronger.</i>

01:10:45.920 --> 01:10:48.878
<i>A beacon of freedom</i>
<i>in a world troubled by shadows.</i>

01:10:49.080 --> 01:10:50.832
<i>America must prevail.</i>

01:10:51.040 --> 01:10:54.316
<i>The future and survival</i>
<i>of modern civilization,</i>

01:10:54.520 --> 01:10:57.080
<i>democracy, freedom,</i>
<i>all depend upon it.</i>

01:10:57.280 --> 01:10:59.236
<i>So your son, Congressman Shaw...</i>

01:10:59.920 --> 01:11:01.717
Rosie.

01:11:08.440 --> 01:11:11.000
I was in the park on Friday?

01:11:11.840 --> 01:11:13.876
We were in the park on Monday.

01:11:15.360 --> 01:11:16.588
Monday?

01:11:17.320 --> 01:11:19.117
- Yep.
- Monday.

01:11:22.480 --> 01:11:25.552
We were flying low.
It's, like, over the ocean, and just...

01:11:26.640 --> 01:11:28.073
A field hospital.

01:11:28.280 --> 01:11:31.397
And they took us up to this place.

01:11:31.600 --> 01:11:33.875
- Where? Military?
- I don't know. I don't know.

01:11:34.080 --> 01:11:35.559
Just state-of-the-art stuff everywhere.

01:11:35.760 --> 01:11:39.912
Stainless steel and wires
and tubes and monitors.

01:11:45.520 --> 01:11:47.670
- Were you tortured?
- No. Yeah.

01:11:47.880 --> 01:11:50.838
I mean, there was pain.
You know, it was like...

01:11:52.880 --> 01:11:55.553
I don't know what they call it.

01:11:56.480 --> 01:11:58.072
Invasive procedure.

01:11:58.280 --> 01:11:59.713
For example?

01:11:59.920 --> 01:12:02.150
Like what? What do you mean?

01:12:15.880 --> 01:12:17.711
Invasive.

01:12:17.920 --> 01:12:19.956
See, they were in my head...

01:12:20.800 --> 01:12:22.791
...and they made me...

01:12:25.440 --> 01:12:28.238
Well, Raymond Shaw,
they made him kill somebody.

01:12:28.440 --> 01:12:29.839
<i>Like it was nothing.</i>

01:12:30.040 --> 01:12:32.349
<i>Private Robert Baker.</i>

01:12:32.560 --> 01:12:33.879
That's who it was, it was a private.

01:12:34.080 --> 01:12:36.435
One of my soldiers.

01:12:37.440 --> 01:12:39.749
I think they made me
kill somebody too.

01:12:41.760 --> 01:12:43.671
<i>A kid named Eddie Ingram.</i>

01:12:43.880 --> 01:12:46.519
Private Ingram, stand up.

01:12:46.720 --> 01:12:49.712
Walk a few steps, please.

01:12:51.200 --> 01:12:54.351
And if you could secure the door,
please, Chris.

01:12:55.360 --> 01:12:56.793
Captain Marco.

01:12:57.000 --> 01:12:58.672
Stand up.

01:13:00.160 --> 01:13:01.559
- Raymond.
- Yes, sir.

01:13:01.760 --> 01:13:03.876
There's a gun on the cupboard.

01:13:04.080 --> 01:13:07.117
Would you please take it
and give it to Captain Marco.

01:13:07.320 --> 01:13:08.753
Yes, sir.

01:13:08.960 --> 01:13:10.188
Here.

01:13:11.920 --> 01:13:12.909
Captain.

01:13:16.560 --> 01:13:18.152
Captain Marco,

01:13:18.360 --> 01:13:20.999
please shoot Private Ingram.

01:13:32.160 --> 01:13:33.559
Now, Raymond,

01:13:33.760 --> 01:13:35.990
suffocate Private Baker.

01:13:36.200 --> 01:13:37.189
Kill him.

01:13:53.480 --> 01:13:55.232
Keep going, Raymond.

01:14:12.360 --> 01:14:15.113
I knew the...
A soldier knows the enemy.

01:14:15.320 --> 01:14:16.912
I'm in command.

01:14:17.120 --> 01:14:19.429
That's primary, I know.

01:14:20.040 --> 01:14:21.792
I thought I knew...

01:14:23.560 --> 01:14:24.595
...who the enemy was.

01:14:24.800 --> 01:14:28.839
My men, they trusted me
with their lives, you know?

01:14:29.040 --> 01:14:30.519
Don't.

01:14:30.720 --> 01:14:32.233
Don't touch me.

01:14:37.040 --> 01:14:39.315
Ben, the person that did this,
what was his name?

01:14:39.520 --> 01:14:41.351
Can you remember?

01:14:42.720 --> 01:14:44.711
Did he have a name?

01:14:48.800 --> 01:14:50.438
Ben?

01:17:42.320 --> 01:17:43.548
Smile if you like.

01:17:46.400 --> 01:17:47.913
This will just take a minute.

01:17:56.400 --> 01:17:57.719
<i>I see you there all the time.</i>

01:17:57.920 --> 01:18:00.115
<i>Bennett Marco.</i>
<i>Checks from First National Bank.</i>

01:18:00.320 --> 01:18:03.756
<i>Romance novels, instant noodles,</i>
<i>NoDoz and tomatoes.</i>

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:07.594
<i>Old friend up there,</i>
<i>an old Army friend that...</i>

01:18:07.800 --> 01:18:10.394
<i>Well, he's in politics now...</i>

01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:14.399
<i>What else did we talk about?</i>

01:18:14.600 --> 01:18:16.670
<i>What happened to you</i>
<i>after you were captured.</i>

01:18:17.520 --> 01:18:18.953
<i>Black helicopters,</i>
<i>secret laboratories...</i>

01:18:22.160 --> 01:18:24.549
<i>... mad scientist, mind drugs...</i>

01:18:25.120 --> 01:18:27.793
<i>... shock torture</i>
<i>and Raymond Shaw.</i>

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:29.956
<i>- You don't believe any of it, do you?</i>
<i>- It's crazy.</i>

01:18:30.160 --> 01:18:31.878
<i>- It sounds crazy, doesn't it?</i>
<i>- It sounds crazy.</i>

01:18:32.080 --> 01:18:33.957
<i>That's what they wanted</i>
<i>me to think too.</i>

01:18:34.160 --> 01:18:35.957
<i>It's exactly what they want</i>
<i>you to think.</i>

01:18:39.000 --> 01:18:41.150
<i>What about the other guys</i>
<i>from your unit?</i>

01:18:41.640 --> 01:18:42.834
<i>Where are they?</i>

01:18:43.040 --> 01:18:47.113
<i>They're all gone.</i>
<i>So-called natural causes.</i>

01:18:47.320 --> 01:18:49.880
<i>Owens died of cancer in '97.</i>

01:18:50.600 --> 01:18:53.478
<i>Villalobos' car crashed.</i>

01:18:53.680 --> 01:18:55.033
<i>Atkins committed suicide.</i>

01:18:55.240 --> 01:18:58.152
<i>Jameson died 9/11, Pentagon.</i>

01:19:00.360 --> 01:19:01.713
<i>- Ben?</i>
<i>- Yeah?</i>

01:19:01.920 --> 01:19:03.956
<i>- Did he have a name?</i>
<i>- Who?</i>

01:19:04.160 --> 01:19:06.674
<i>The person that did this, Ben.</i>

01:19:06.880 --> 01:19:09.599
<i>What was his name?</i>
<i>Can you remember?</i>

01:19:11.200 --> 01:19:12.394
<i>Ben.</i>

01:19:12.600 --> 01:19:14.318
<i>- Yeah?</i>
<i>- Did he have a name?</i>

01:20:14.040 --> 01:20:16.508
<i>You only have to look</i>
<i>at the enormous strides made</i>

01:20:16.720 --> 01:20:18.790
<i>in the last decade</i>
<i>with the genetic reconfiguration</i>

01:20:19.000 --> 01:20:20.991
<i>of the noble tomato.</i>

01:20:21.200 --> 01:20:23.873
<i>What was happening was the tomato</i>
<i>was over-ripening in the process</i>

01:20:24.080 --> 01:20:25.798
<i>and it was losing its flavor.</i>

01:20:26.000 --> 01:20:29.390
<i>It's actually a very simple procedure</i>
<i>to deactivate the gene concerned.</i>

01:20:29.600 --> 01:20:32.831
<i>And the same thing</i>
<i>can be applied to ourselves.</i>

01:20:33.040 --> 01:20:34.029
<i>At a flick of a switch,</i>

01:20:34.240 --> 01:20:36.959
<i>we can adjust character,</i>

01:20:37.160 --> 01:20:38.798
<i>change personality.</i>

01:20:39.000 --> 01:20:41.389
<i>And of course, more importantly...</i>

01:20:42.240 --> 01:20:45.232
<i>... we can offset</i>
<i>the ravages of dementia</i>

01:20:45.440 --> 01:20:50.195
<i>by implanting memory or adjusting</i>
<i>the synaptic connections.</i>

01:20:50.400 --> 01:20:53.676
<i>We can free people</i>
<i>from the terrible burden</i>

01:20:53.880 --> 01:20:56.075
<i>of an emotionally</i>
<i>compromised past.</i>

01:21:00.200 --> 01:21:01.553
- Watch where you're going!
- Sorry.

